lon
	goes from 0 to 360 in 576 intervals, for .625 deg per interval


lat
	goes from -90 to 90 in 360 intervals, for .5 deg per interval


time
	in minutes for a given day


Palau, for instance, with

latMin=0
latMax=15
lonMin=125
lonMax=145

would take (approximately)

	lat[180:1:210]

	lon[200:1:232]


https://goldsmr4.gesdisc.eosdis.nasa.gov/thredds/dodsC/MERRA2_aggregation/M2T1NXRAD.5.12.4/M2T1NXRAD.5.12.4_Aggregation_2022.ncml?lon[200:1:232],lat[180:1:210],time[0:1:7295],SWGDN[0:1:7295][180:1:210][200:1:232]
